news.title: Nagpur civic body rolls back 100% hike in building plan sanction charges
news.para: Municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B has implemented revised building plan charges from January 1, which will cost the cash-strapped civic body revenue loss of around Rs75 crore per annum.

news.title: Canada bans most foreigners from buying homes
news.para: In late December, Ottawa also clarified that the ban would apply only to city dwellings and not to recreational properties such as summer cottages.

news.title: Twitter sued for nonpayment of rent on San Francisco office
news.para: The landlord, Columbia Reit - 650 California LLC, says it notified Twitter on Dec. 16 that it would be in default on its lease for the 30th floor of the Hartford Building in five days unless the rent was paid.

news.title: Pune civic body's property tax earnings surpass Rs 1,500-crore mark in FY23
news.para: Data from the civic body showed the revenue till December-end, boosted by the addition of new areas to PMC limits, was around Rs 225 crore more than the collections during the same period during the last financial year, 2021-22.

news.title: Kerala government gives nod for Sabarimala airport land acquisition
news.para: The proposed plan of the state government is to construct the airport at Cheruvally Estate near Erumeli. In addition, 370 acres outside the estate will also be acquired as per the new order.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh govt banking on newly-developed land banks to attract investments in GIS
news.para: The government claims to have 1.22 lakh hectare land bank in the state. Some of the key land parcels that are expected to be showcased to industries in the summit will be areas close to Pithampur, Dewas and Ratlam.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh housing department directs development bodies to solve building plan woes
news.para: Directives have been issued by the department on December 28 and authorities will start organising the samadhan diwas from January 5 onwards.

news.title: Poor response to meet property tax deadline in Ludhiana
news.para: The officials claimed that now they will begin with sealing exercises from next month, so as to ensure that each and every defaulter is forced to pay the tax.

news.title: Vijayawada civic body to focus on housing project as revenues soar
news.para: The civic body realised 51.9 crore revenue from building plan approvals. Property tax revenues jumped from 65 crore in 2021 to 110 crore in 2022.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA developed most number of layouts in 2022
news.para: The VMRDA developed 81 layouts spread in about 5,000 acres under the Jagananna Colonies alone in 2022 by spending about ₹150 crore to create basic infrastructure.

news.title: Building curbs near naval units cut, will boost Mumbai redevelopment projects
news.para: In a major relief for civilians living near naval installations across India, especially in Mumbai, the defence ministry has reduced construction restrictions near the establishments to just 50 metres from 500 metres.

news.title: TIDCO extends date for bids to identify consultant for Parandur airport
news.para: The consultant will carry out the study, prepare a report,and identify builders for the new airport in the 4,500 acres of the land already ear-marked for the project around 70km away from the city.

news.title: Fire safety regulations draft still not finalized in Gujarat
news.para: The state government prepared a draft of the Gujarat Fire Prevention and Life Safety Measures Regulations, 2021, to eliminate certain discrepancies in the provisions of the National Building Code (NBC) and the General Development Control Regulations (GDCR).

news.title: GST not payable on house rented to proprietor for residential purpose: CBIC
news.para: ​The Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs (CBIC) also notified amendments in GST rates effective from January 1, 2023 for certain goods and services, as per the recommendations of the GST Council in its meeting on December 17.

news.title: Office space absorption in six cities touch 54.8 million sq ft in 2022: Savills India
news.para: Bengaluru recorded its all-time peak at 17.3 million sq ft; and so did NCR and Chennai at 11.3 million sq ft and 7.3 million sq ft respectively. New supply rose by 45.1% at 53.4 million sq ft when compared to 2021.
